      • skipGeneric

        public int skipGeneric(java.util.List<IToken> tokens,
                       int startIndex)
        Skips a generic or template declaration in the given token list that begins at the given start index. The token at the given index must be of type ETokenType.LT. The index of the matching closing token is returned. In C++ constructs like "std::vector<SomeType<(1>2)>>" are allowed, thus we cannot simply skip to the matching closing token.
        Overrides:
        skipGeneric in class CLikeLanguageFeatureParserBase

      • skipGenericReverse

        public int skipGenericReverse(java.util.List<IToken> tokens,
                              int startIndex)
        Skips a generic parameter (nested < and >) in reverse direction and returns the index of the first opening < token. Tje token at the given index must be of type ETokenType.GT. The index of the matching opening token is returned. In C++ constructs like "std::vector<SomeType<(1>2)>>" are allowed, thus we cannot simply skip to the matching closing token.
        Overrides:
        skipGenericReverse in class CLikeLanguageFeatureParserBase
